\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Question: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All these abstract definitions notwithstanding, would it be all right if
 I always keep in the back of my mind that a vector 
\series bold

\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}$
\end_inset


\series default
 is a row of components 
\begin_inset Formula $(v_{1},...,v_{n})$
\end_inset

?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Answer:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It will be perfectly all right 
\emph on
as long as
\emph default
 you work with 
\emph on
finite
\emph default
-dimen\SpecialChar \-
sion\SpecialChar \-
al vector spaces.
 (This intuition often fails when working with infinite-dimen\SpecialChar \-
sion\SpecialChar \-
al spaces!)
 Even if all we need is finite-dimen\SpecialChar \-
sion\SpecialChar \-
al vectors, there is another argument
