 This set is linearly dependent because there exists a nontrivial linear
 combination (i.e.\InsetSpace ~
a linear combination with 
\emph on
some
\emph default
 nonzero coefficients) which is equal to zero, 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\mathbf{u}-2\mathbf{v}=1\mathbf{u}+\left(-2\right)\mathbf{v}+0\mathbf{w}=0.\]

\end_inset

