 This subset forms an infinite-dimen\SpecialChar \-
sion\SpecialChar \-
al vector space because the term-by-term
 sum of two convergent series is again a convergent series.
 Consider, on the other hand, the set of infinite sequences 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(a_{0},a_{1},a_{2},...\right)$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{j}\in\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 are such that the series 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{j=0}^{\infty}\left|a_{j}\right|^{2}$
\end_inset

 converges.
 This set also forms an infinite-dimen\SpecialChar \-
sion\SpecialChar \-
al vector space.
