\begin_inset Formula $V\oplus W$
\end_inset

 has a certain subspace which is canonically isomorphic to 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

.
 This subspace is the set of all vectors from 
\begin_inset Formula $V\oplus W$
\end_inset

 of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\mathbf{v},0\right)$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}\in V$
