\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}\in V$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{v}\otimes1$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, there is a canonical isomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $V\rightarrow V\otimes\mathbb{K}$
\end_inset

 which maps 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}$
\end_inset

