\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a},\mathbf{b},\mathbf{c}$
\end_inset

 that change sign under exchange of any two vectors.
 The expression in Eq.\InsetSpace ~
(
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{eq:antisym 3}

\end_inset

) will be denoted for brevity by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a}\wedge\mathbf{b}\wedge\mathbf{c}$
\end_inset

, similarly to the exterior product of two vectors, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a}\otimes\mathbf{b}-\mathbf{b}\otimes\mathbf{a}$
\end_inset

, which is denoted for brevity by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a}\wedge\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

.
 Here is a general definition.
\end_layout

