 We also have a computational procedure for determining the subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{Span}\, S$
\end_inset

 together with its dimension.
 Thus, we find that a 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

-dimen\SpecialChar \-
sion\SpecialChar \-
al subspace is adequately specified by selecting a nonzero tensor
 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega\in\wedge^{k}V$
\end_inset

