\end_inset

 into an exterior product of vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \mathbf{v}_{i}\,|\, i=1,...,k\right\} $
\end_inset

 is not unique, but any such decomposition yields a set 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \mathbf{v}_{i}\,|\, i=1,...,k\right\} $
