\end_inset

, that is, a multiplication by a number.
 This is precisely the map we have been using in the previous section to
 define the determinant.
 In this notation, we have
\begin_inset Formula \[
\det\hat{A}\equiv\big({\wedge^{N}\hat{A}^{N}}{\big)}^{\wedge T}.\]

\end_inset

Here we identify 
