\begin_inset Formula \[
\wedge^{N-1}\hat{A}^{N-n+1}(\mathbf{v}_{1}\wedge...\wedge\mathbf{v}_{n}\wedge\mathbf{e}_{n+1}\wedge...\mathbf{e}_{N})=0\]

\end_inset

 since at least one operator 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

 must act on some 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}_{i}$
\end_inset

, which yields zero within the exterior product.
