\begin_inset Formula $\hat{P}$
\end_inset

 or any other projector only onto 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{e}_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 This can be seen as follows.
 We note that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}\hat{A}=0$
\end_inset

, and thus any polynomial in 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

 can be rewritten as 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{0}\hat{1}_{V}+a_{1}\hat{A}$
\end_inset

.
