\begin_layout Paragraph
Example 2:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider the space of polynomials in 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 of degree at most 1, i.e.\InsetSpace ~
the space spanned by 
\begin_inset Formula $\{\underbar{1},\underbar{x},\underbar{y}\}$
\end_inset

, and the operator
\begin_inset Formula \[
\hat{A}=x\frac{\partial}{\partial x}+\frac{\partial}{\partial y}.\]

\end_inset

The characteristic polynomial of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

