3 with 
\begin_inset Formula $n=2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $N=3$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{0}=q_{1}=0$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{2}=q_{3}=1$
\end_inset

.
 The system of equations for the coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{k}$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
q_{2}c_{1}+q_{3}c_{2} & =0,\\
q_{2}c_{2} & =1,\end{align*}

\end_inset

and the solution is 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{1}=-1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{2}=1$
\end_inset

.
 We note that in our example,
\begin_inset Formula \[
\hat{A}^{2}=x\frac{\partial}{\partial x}.\]

\end_inset

So we can compute the projector 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{P}_{0}$
\end_inset

