\emph on
Hint
\emph default
: Use a basis of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \mathbf{x}_{1},\mathbf{v}_{2},...,\mathbf{v}_{n},\mathbf{e}_{n+1},...,\mathbf{e}_{N}\right\} $
\end_inset

 as in Exercise\InsetSpace ~
2.
 
