\begin_inset Formula $*(\mathbf{a}\wedge\mathbf{b})$
\end_inset

 is linear in both 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

, and then to consider the pairwise vector products 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{e}_{1}\times\mathbf{e}_{2}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{e}_{2}\times\mathbf{e}_{3},$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{e}_{3}\times\mathbf{e}_{1}$
\end_inset

 for an orthonormal basis 
